<h2>🌍 The Problem</h2>

<p>Pakistan has <strong>33 million diabetics</strong> — the <strong>3rd highest in the world.</strong><br>
Over <strong>50% remain undiagnosed.</strong><br><br>
Community health workers running rural screening camps have no fast intelligent triage tool.
They screen hundreds of patients manually with no way to prioritize who needs urgent referral.<br><br>
<strong>GlucoseGuard PK changes that.</strong></p>

---

<h2>🩺 What It Does</h2>

<table>
  <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>🎯 Risk Prediction</td><td>Instant diabetes risk score from basic health indicators</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟢🟡🔴 Risk Levels</td><td>Clear Low / Medium / High classification</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔍 SHAP Explainability</td><td>Top 5 risk drivers explained in plain language</td></tr>
  <tr><td>📋 Referral Guidance</td><td>Lifestyle advice / Retest / Refer for HbA1c</td></tr>
  <tr><td>👥 Population Summary</td><td>Camp-level screening insights for NGO health workers</td></tr>
</table>

---

<h2>📊 Machine Learning Pipeline</h2>

<table>
  <tr><th>Stage</th><th>Details</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Dataset</td><td>CDC BRFSS 2015 — 80,000+ health records</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Models Evaluated</td><td>Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Selected Model</td><td>Logistic Regression</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Diabetic Recall</td><td><strong>76%</strong></td></tr>
  <tr><td>ROC-AUC Score</td><td><strong>0.81</strong></td></tr>
  <tr><td>Class Imbalance</td><td>Handled with SMOTE</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Explainability</td><td>SHAP LinearExplainer</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Deployment</td><td>Streamlit Cloud</td></tr>
</table>

<br>

<h3>🤔 Why Logistic Regression?</h3>

<p>For a health screening tool, <strong>missing a diabetic patient is dangerous.</strong><br><br>
Logistic Regression achieved <strong>76% recall on diabetic cases</strong> compared to XGBoost's 18% —
making it the clinically safer and more responsible choice for community triage support.</p>

